# VQE — Variational Quantum Eigensolver

A general-purpose Variational Quantum Eigensolver built from scratch in Q# and Python. Given any molecule, this system automatically generates its Hamiltonian as a Pauli string using quantum chemistry libraries and finds the ground state energy using a hybrid classical-quantum optimization loop.**Not Vibecoded**

---

## Features

**Quantum Circuit (Q#)**
- 4-qubit hardware-efficient ansatz with 2 entangling layers
- Each layer consists of Ry rotations on all qubits followed by a CNOT chain (linear entanglement)
- 16 variational parameters total across both layers
- General expectation value operation that accepts any Pauli term at runtime — no hardcoded measurement functions
- Automatic basis rotation: H gate for X measurements, S†H for Y measurements, identity for Z
- Parity-based multi-qubit measurement — only measures qubits relevant to each Pauli term, reducing noise

**Hamiltonian Generation (Python + PySCF + OpenFermion)**
- Accepts any molecule as atomic geometry input
- Runs Hartree-Fock calculation via PySCF to obtain molecular integrals
- Applies Jordan-Wigner transformation via OpenFermion to convert fermionic Hamiltonian to qubit Pauli operators
- Parses the resulting QubitOperator into a clean Python dictionary of Pauli terms and coefficients
- Supports custom basis sets, molecular charge, and spin multiplicity

**Classical Optimization (Python + SciPy)**
- COBYLA optimizer via scipy.optimize.minimize
- Multi-start strategy — runs optimizer from multiple random initial parameter sets and keeps the best result
- Configurable number of shots, optimizer runs, and basis set per molecule call

**General VQE Runner**
- Single `run_vqe()` function call handles the entire pipeline end to end
- Molecule-agnostic — pass any atomic geometry, charge, and multiplicity
- Outputs ground state energy in Hartrees and kJ/mol
- Prints optimal variational parameters

---

## Tested Molecules - can support many more

| Molecule | Formula | Notes |
|----------|---------|-------|
| Hydrogen | H₂ | Primary test case, ~0.01 Hartree from exact |
| Lithium Hydride | LiH | Larger system, recommended shots ≥ 2000 |
| Helium Hydride | HeH⁺ | Charged system, charge=1 |
| Water | H₂O | Slower, recommend shots ≥ 2000 |
| Beryllium Hydride | BeH₂ | Larger system |

